## Key Features

### User-Facing
- ✅ Simple command: `/template generate deal <excel.xlsx>`
- ✅ Clear progress: Step 1/5, 2/5, 3/5, 4/5, 5/5
- ✅ Visual indicators: 🔄 in_progress, ✅ completed, ⏳ pending
- ✅ Statistics output (fields extracted, placeholders created)
- ✅ Next steps guidance

### Internal (Hidden from Users)
- ✅ Excel parsing complexity
- ✅ Field name mappings
- ✅ AI module logic
- ✅ Standard module database lookups
- ✅ Template structure details
- ✅ Placeholder ID generation
- ✅ Calculation formulas

### Quality Checks
- ✅ Clean template content (no source references)
- ✅ Complete reasoning (all sources documented)
- ✅ Organized checklist (sorted by section)
- ✅ Consistent formatting
- ✅ Proper placeholder IDs

## Next Steps Workflow

After template generation, users should:

1. **Review checklist**: Open `{Project}_checklist.md`
2. **Fill answers**: Add presale confirmations in "Presale's Answer" column
3. **Update template**: Replace `[Value] [PLACEHOLDER_ID]` with confirmed values
4. **Remove placeholders**: Clean template should have no placeholders
5. **Generate slides**: Use `/quotation generate slide {Project}_template.md`

## Integration with Quotation Workflow

```
/template generate deal DT_0109.xlsx
  ↓
Generates 3 files:
  • DT_0109_template.md (with placeholders)
  • DT_0109_reasoning.md
  • DT_0109_checklist.md
  ↓
Presale reviews checklist, fills answers
  ↓
Updates template with confirmed values
  ↓
/quotation generate slide DT_0109_template.md
  ↓
Generates:
  • DT_0109_proposal.pptx
  • DT_0109_proposal.pdf
```
